[b][size=4]Pause for Backups[/size][/b]

Wrap your backup jobs with pause/unpause over SSH so Unspin doesn't inflate counters while the backup tool reads your files:

[code]ssh root@nas /etc/rc.d/rc.unspin pause borgbackup
borg create ssh://root@nas/mnt/disk1/backups::daily /data
ssh root@nas /etc/rc.d/rc.unspin unpause borgbackup[/code]

Locks stack - multiple backup tools can pause independently without interfering with each other.

[b][size=4]Requirements[/size][/b]

[list]
[*]Unraid 7.0+ (probably even earlier, but tested with 7.2.3 onwards)
[*]No external dependencies - single C++ binary
[/list]

